__done__:
__done__( [error:Error|null[, results:any]] )
    Callback invoked to confirm that an asynchronous command has finished
    executing.
require:
require( id:string )
    Imports a module, JSON, or local file.
alias2pkg:
alias2pkg( alias:any )
    Returns the package name associated with a provided alias.

alias2pkg( instance:any )
    Returns the package name associated with a provided class instance.
alias2related:
alias2related( alias:any )
    Returns aliases related to a specified alias.

alias2related( instance:any )
    Returns aliases associated with a provided class instance.
ans:
ans
    Result of the last successfully executed command.
assignfrom:
assignfrom( workspace:string, variable:string|symbol )
    Reads a value from a specified workspace.
assignin:
assignin( workspace:string, variable:string|symbol, value:any )
    Assigns a value to a variable in a specified workspace.
citation:
citation()
    Prints how to cite stdlib in publications.
clear:
clear()
    Clears the entire REPL screen and scrollback history.
clearVars:
clearVars( [options] )
    Deletes user-defined variables in the current workspace.
clearWorkspace:
clearWorkspace( [name, ][options] )
    Deletes user-defined variables in a specified workspace.
contributors:
contributors()
    Prints the list of contributors.
currentWorkspace:
currentWorkspace
    Name of the current workspace.
deeprerequire:
deeprerequire( id:string )
    Re-imports a module, JSON, or local file and all its associated module
    dependencies.
evalin:
evalin( workspace:string, expression:string )
    Evaluates an expression in a specified workspace.
example:
example( alias:any )
    Runs examples for a specified alias.

example( property:any )
    Runs examples for a specified property.

example( instance:any )
    Runs examples for a provided class instance.
help:
help()
    Prints help text.

help( alias:any )
    Prints help text for a specified alias.

help( property:any )
    Prints help text for a specified property.

help( instance:any )
    Prints help text for a provided class instance.
info:
info( alias:any )
    Prints abbreviated help text for a specified alias.

info( property:any )
    Prints abbreviated help text for a specified property.

info( instance:any )
    Prints abbreviated help text for a provided class instance.
isKeyword:
isKeyword( keyword:string )
    Returns a boolean indicating whether a string is a reserved keyword in the
    REPL environment.
isWorkspace:
isWorkspace( name:string|RegExp )
    Returns a boolean indicating whether a specified workspace exists.
load:
load( fpath:string )
    Loads and evaluates a JavaScript file, such as a REPL history file, line-by-
    line.
loadWorkspace:
loadWorkspace( name[, options] )
    Loads variables from a specified workspace into the current workspace.
logStart:
logStart( fpath:string )
    Starts logging commands and printed output to a specified file path.
logStop:
logStop( id:number )
    Stops logging commands and printed output to a file path associated with a
    specified record identifier.
renameWorkspace:
renameWorkspace( oldName:string, newName:string )
    Renames a workspace.
rerequire:
rerequire( id:string )
    Re-imports a module, JSON, or local file.
save:
save( fpath:string )
    Saves previous commands to a specified file path.
saveStart:
saveStart( fpath:string )
    Starts saving commands to a specified file path.
saveStop:
saveStop( id:number )
    Stops saving commands to a file path associated with a specified record
    identifier.
userDoc:
userDoc( alias:string, [ref:any,] doc:string )
    Adds user-defined documentation.
vars:
vars( [options] )
    Returns a list of variable names in the current workspace.
varsWorkspace:
varsWorkspace( [name, ][options] )
    Returns a list of variable names in a specified workspace.
workspace:
workspace( name:string )
    Switches to a specified workspace.
workspaces:
workspaces( [options] )
    Returns a list of workspace names.
